sentence: DuPont ( DD ) announced that it has collaborated with Procter & Gamble ( PG ), to use cellulosic ethanol in North American Tide Cold Water laundry detergent.
The application will be first of its kind.
The cellulosic ethanol will replace corn-based ethanol in the formulation.
DuPont will produce cellulosic ethanol at its new biorefinery in Nevada, IA., which is currently under construction.
Once completed, the plant will be the biggest bioethanol refinery in the world, with a capacity to produce 30 million gallons of cellulosic ethanol per year-a process with zero net carbon emissions.
As one of the world's largest laundry manufacturers, Procter & Gamble has a responsibility to lead renewable sourcing in products.
The company ensures that consumers will still get the great Tide laundry performance they want, while further reducing the impact on environment.
As stated by Procter & Gamble, the product will "re-purpose" about 7,000 tons of agricultural waste per year.
With this deal, DuPont is diversifying its portfolio for cellulosic ethanol beyond fuels.
The company will continue to look for new opportunities and new collaborations to transform value chains with more sustainable solutions.
DuPont strives to play a pivotal role in various sectors such as industries, aerospace and sports to name a few.
Better-ranked stocks worth considering in the chemical space include Valhi Inc. ( VHI ) and LyondellBasell Industries N.V. ( LYB ).
